CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 23, 1963, pg. 22 reads: "Bulldog Bucket - Following a whirlpool of action. Westinghouse High School's Richard White (54) is seen ringing two points for the Bulldogs, as teammate Jesse Murphy (20) leaps for a tap-in, if necessary.  Another Westinghouse player, Kelso Gordon (44), is seen in forecourt.  The three players of Peabody High are Jay Leipzig (33), Art Love (51) and, in the backcourt, Paul Levin (10).  Peabody upset the Homewooders, 45-43. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Basketball game between Westinghouse and Peabody High Schools, including Peabody players Jay Leipzig (33), Art Love (51), and Paul Levin (10), and Westinghouse player Kelso Gordon (44)
